}

/* Subheading */
.subhead {
    -fx-font-size: 14px;
    -fx-font-weight: bold;
    -fx-text-fill: #2b3a67;
}

How to build & run (quick)

Create a Java project with package root app.

Put Main.java in src/app, MainController.java in src/app/controllers, EmailValidator.java in src/app/models.

Place main_view.fxml and style.css under resources/ at the resource root so getResource("/main_view.fxml") finds it.

Add JavaFX SDK to your VM args / module path. Example VM args (adjust to your JavaFX SDK path):

--module-path "C:\javafx-sdk-20\lib" --add-modules javafx.controls,javafx.fxml


Run app.Main.

If you use Maven/Gradle I can give the pom.xml or build.gradle ‚Äî tell me which.







üìò PROJECT GUIDE ‚Äî Email Format Validator (JavaFX GUI Application)
1. ABSTRACT

The Email Format Validator is a JavaFX-based desktop application that verifies whether an email address entered by a user follows standard email formatting rules.
Using robust regular expressions and real-time input validation, the application ensures accurate and fast verification. Its clean and modern GUI design, built using JavaFX, enhances usability and creates a professional user experience.

This project demonstrates practical application of Java, JavaFX, regex (regular expressions), MVC design, and GUI development ‚Äî making it suitable for academic submissions and professional portfolios.

2. INTRODUCTION

With online services increasing, validating user email input has become essential to prevent invalid entries, authentication failures, and security risks.
Incorrect email formats often lead to:

Failed registrations

Login errors

System inconsistencies

Email Format Validator automates email structure verification by following industry-standard patterns used in websites and applications.

3. PROBLEM STATEMENT

Many online forms allow users to enter invalid email addresses.
This results in:

Incorrect or unreachable user accounts

Data inconsistencies

Failed communication

There is a need for a simple, accurate, fast, and user-friendly email validation tool.

4. OBJECTIVES

The Email Format Validator aims to:

Validate user-entered email addresses in real-time

Provide instant feedback (Valid / Invalid)

Use accurate regex to match email standards

Provide a modern, interactive GUI

Follow clean MVC architecture for scalability

5. EXISTING SYSTEM

Existing systems include:

Basic web forms

Browser-based validators

Limitations:

No offline desktop application

Inconsistent email patterns

Poor GUI

Not highly interactive

No modular architecture

6. PROPOSED SYSTEM

The proposed system features:

JavaFX GUI

Dynamic validation

Accurate RFC-compliant regex pattern

Error messages for incorrect formats

Attractive UI with animations and colors

Easy-to-use interface

7. SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS
Hardware Requirements

Intel i3 or higher CPU

4GB RAM

50 MB free storage

Software Requirements

JDK 17+

JavaFX SDK

IntelliJ / Eclipse / NetBeans

Windows / macOS / Linux

8. METHODOLOGY
Techniques used:

JavaFX for GUI

